    <p>Just a short message from me today. I want to briefly tell you about my Christmas Eve here in Sydney.</p>
    <p>It's pleasantly warm outside today, but unfortunately it keeps raining on and off. Plus, we three German guys stayed up way too late last night, peacefully celebrating the start of the holidays. So today we took things a bit easier. We did some light cooking and baked Christmas cookies.</p>
    <p>Tonight was the highlight of the day. We all decided to go out to eat together. Not just anywhere, but to a German restaurant for a traditional Christmas roast. Unfortunately, like everything else in Australia, it wasn't exactly cheap, but thankfully there are some dear people in my life.</p>
